<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-65-0872 </DOCNO><TEXT>This book translates the controversy surrounding nuclear issues into abalanced curriculum. The publication covers all aspects of nuclear power,including atomic structure, nuclear fission, the fuel cycle, how nuclearplants work, nuclear waste disposal, radiation, nuclear weapons and emergencyplanning. It was developed by pro and anti-nuclear groups. It not onlyencourages technical knowledge but also addresses values and moral dilemmas,and deals with controversy in such a way as to motivate learning.</TEXT></DOC>